# M15b cross-module extern FFI obligation canary. `a.puts` is an
# imported extern; calling it from another module STILL requires a
# `raw` block at the call site, per M22 entry 35: "extern
# declarations are the FFI boundary; the safety bargain across
# them requires explicit acknowledgment." Pre-M15b, the obligation
# evaporated at the module edge.
use a

sub main()
  a.puts("hi")
